721651f-a.title: Manhattan: Minetta Lane - MacDougal Street
721651f-a.text:
Minetta Lane, north side, from but not including MacDougal
Street, west to the intersection of Sixth Ave., and Carmine Street.
This lane will soon be modernised.
1923.
Gift of E. M. Jenks.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

721162f-a.title: Manhattan: MacDougal Street - Minetta Lane
721162f-a.text:
115, 117 Macdougal Street, at and adjoining the N.W. corner of Minetta
Lane, south of West 3rd (formerly Amity) Street. No. 115 is
(obviously) an old stable. Notice the beam proiecting over the tall
upper window in the center. A pulley was fastened to this so that
bales of hay could be hoisted up into the hayloft.
May 23, 1933.
L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
